sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(Workload Controller)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler
    participant JobCtrl as Kueue Job Controller<br/>(batch/Job, Kubeflow, Ray)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Job Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Submit Job (e.g., PyTorchJob)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission Webhook<br/>POST /mutate-*<br/>mTLS (API server cert)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Job mutated (suspended=true,<br/>queue-name label added)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)

    Note over Controller,Scheduler: Flow 3: Workload Scheduling Lifecycle

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Watch: Workload CR created<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>Controller: Enqueue to internal<br/>queue manager

    Scheduler->>Scheduler: 4. Scheduling cycle:<br/>assign flavors,<br/>check quotas,<br/>evaluate preemption
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: 5. Update Workload status<br/>(admission=granted)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    JobCtrl->>K8sAPI: 6. Patch Job: suspend=false<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>JobCtrl: Job unsuspended,<br/>pods created

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA token)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(queue depths, admission<br/>latency, resource usage)
